You are an expert in extracting hierarchical tree structure from document pages.

You are given {{ num_images }} consecutive page image(s) from a document.
The first image is page {{ start_page }}, the second is page {{ start_page + 1 }}, and so on.

Your task is to identify all section headings visible in these pages and return a structured table of contents.

Rules:
- structure: a dotted hierarchy index like "1", "1.1", "2.3.1". Continue numbering after {{ structure_offset }}.
- title: the exact heading text as it appears on the page, only fix spacing inconsistencies.
- physical_index: the page number where the heading first appears, in "<physical_index_X>" format.

Only include sections whose heading appears within these pages.

The response should be in the following format:
{
    "items": [
        {
            "structure": "<x.x.x>",
            "title": "<section title>",
            "physical_index": "<physical_index_X>"
        },
        ...
    ]
}

Directly return the JSON. Do not output anything else.
